<script type="text/javascript"><![CDATA[$(document).ready(function() {
        var locations = [[],{"id":"black_mountain_gold_chocolates","lat":51.8597837,"lon":-3.1348563,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Black Mountain Gold Chocolates","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3467"}},{"id":"black_mountains_smokery","lat":51.8538796,"lon":-3.1307875,"enhanced":true,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Black Mountains Smokery","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_5669__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Black Mountains Smokery is a family-run gourmet food business based in the Brecon Beacons, South Wales. Our award-winning smoked foods are carefully sourced from British suppliers and traditionally cured and smoked at our smokehouse in Crickhowell. Local artisan food at its best. Fresh Food - Friendly Service - Reliable Delivery\r\nFreshly prepared&nbsp;smoked salmon, trout, chicken, duck &amp; cheese and smoked&nbsp;food gift hampers&nbsp;for&nbsp;home delivery&nbsp;, (no minimum order, delivery charge from &pound;4.95). Buy&nbsp;online&nbsp;or&nbsp;download our latest pricelist&nbsp;and simply post&nbsp;or phone&nbsp;for orders, enquiries &amp; any further information. Our phone lines are open from 8.30am &ndash; 4.30pm on normal weekdays. &nbsp;\r\nTrade Enquiries\r\nWe supply chefs, caterers, caf&eacute;s, farm shops and delis. &nbsp;If you are a trade customer, please request our&nbsp;wholesale prices.","url":"\/businesses\/3509"}},{"id":"bookish","lat":51.8583347,"lon":-3.135938,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Bookish","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3423"}},{"id":"bridge_end_inn","lat":51.857034,"lon":-3.1402614,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Bridge End Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3192"}},{"id":"bridgend_inn","lat":51.8184283,"lon":-3.068124,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Bridgend Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3213"}},{"id":"britannia_inn","lat":51.8589228,"lon":-3.1374194,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Britannia Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3219"}},{"id":"cambrian_inn","lat":51.8100881,"lon":-3.1179995,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Cambrian Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3218"}},{"id":"cordell_country_inn","lat":51.8162818,"lon":-3.0589046,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Cordell Country Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3186"}},{"id":"corn_exchange","lat":51.8585462,"lon":-3.1373083,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Corn Exchange","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3185"}},{"id":"crickhowell_adventure","lat":51.9475802,"lon":-3.392278,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Crickhowell Adventure","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3440"}},{"id":"crickhowell_news","lat":51.8585462,"lon":-3.1373083,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Crickhowell News","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3403"}},{"id":"crickhowell_resource_and_information_centre","lat":51.8583347,"lon":-3.135938,"enhanced":null,"popup":{"title":"Crickhowell Resource and Information Centre","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/2721"}},{"id":"deja_vu_antiques","lat":51.859160450175,"lon":-3.136682510376,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Deja Vu Antiques","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3426"}},{"id":"fe_richards","lat":51.8585462,"lon":-3.1373083,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"FE Richards","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3404"}},{"id":"gallery_on_the_usk","lat":51.8585462,"lon":-3.1373083,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Gallery on the Usk","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3311"}},{"id":"glan_y_dwr","lat":51.86038,"lon":-3.13966,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Glan y Dwr Bed and Breakfast","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_2939__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Alison and Julian welcome you to Glan y Dwr, a Five Star accredited Bed and Breakfast in the centre of the charming small town of Crickhowell. We offer high standards of accommodation with all bedrooms having large en-suite bathrooms, with lovely guest areas and breakfast facilities, and are recipients of a Gold Award in 2014 from Visit Wales. All rooms have extensive views over the beautiful local mountains and we have a garden to relax in when the weather is favourable.On the doorstep, are good pubs, restaurants and shopping facilities - and why not try one of the thirteen \"Cracking Walks in Crickhowell\" when you want to stretch your legs. Once you have parked your car in our drive, if you so wish, you can settle in and relax without needing to use the car again until you leave.","url":"\/businesses\/2741"}},{"id":"glanusk_estate","lat":51.8675703,"lon":-3.1751385,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Glanusk Estate","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_4808__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"The Glanusk Estate is a private, family-owned Estate in the beautiful countryside of the Usk Valley in South Wales, just 2 and a half hours from London. Set within 400 acres of parkland, The Estate offers bespoke accommodation including holiday lets and exclusive, fully catered house parties, a range of sporting activities including fishing and clay pigeon shooting, and a selection of unique wedding sites. The private chapel is available for wedding blessings, and the grounds offer wonderful vistas for photographs. The Estate is home for The Green Man festival, and a number of other events including the endurance event, Tough Mudder, and a season of outdoor theatre performances during the summer months. It is also a popular venue for corporate executive meetings and team building events.","url":"\/businesses\/2742"}},{"id":"gwyn_deri_bed_and_breakfast","lat":51.8593347,"lon":-3.1403776,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Gwyn Deri Bed and Breakfast","image":"","text":"Gwyn Deri Bed and Breakfast is situated a few minutes walk from the centre of quiet and peaceful Crickhowell, which is a pretty town in the historical and cultural Brecon Beacons National Park, lying to the south of the Black Mountains in the valley of the River Usk.Brian and Kathy would like to welcome you to their bed and breakfast in Crickhowell. We provide a warm welcome with our beautifully decorated and well equipped rooms, with open views of the spectacular countryside - and of course our wonderfully wholesome breakfasts made from locally sourced produce.We are walker, cyclist and biker friendly with a drying room and secure storage space for cycles and motorbikes.We are Brecon Beacons, Dark Skies and Geopark Ambassodors with a host of local knowledge of the area.","url":"\/businesses\/2752"}},{"id":"hall_farm","lat":51.8438342,"lon":-3.0926063,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Hall Farm","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_5688__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Three or four pretty bedrooms sleeping 5 or 7 in two buildings. &nbsp;Games room. &nbsp;Three bathrooms.Located on the eastern edge of the National Park on Sugar Loaf slopes. &nbsp;The Hall Farm is a 100 ha traditional hill farm with a sheep walk on Sugar Loaf and the hill gate above the barn. &nbsp;Only one cottage on the farm and offers an exclusive location. &nbsp;Walks from the front door. &nbsp;During autumn, winter and spring the barn provides accommadation in the courtyard bedroom for walkers and cyclists from &pound;45.00 per night per room, wet room with shower, breakfast is always provided(continental). Information email available. Crickhowell 2 miles.Great linen, all welsh toiletries, groceries and provisions.","url":"\/businesses\/2754"}},{"id":"horseshoe_inn","lat":51.8530746,"lon":-3.1461432,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Horseshoe Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3182"}},{"id":"lamb_and_flag","lat":51.8309547,"lon":-3.0439240000001,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Lamb and Flag","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3202"}},{"id":"llanwenarth_hotel___riverside_restaurant","lat":51.8382653,"lon":-3.083616,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Llanwenarth Riverside Restaurant","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3347"}},{"id":"m_t__cashell","lat":51.8585462,"lon":-3.1373083,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"M T  Cashell","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3425"}},{"id":"manor_hotel","lat":51.8660133,"lon":-3.1405756,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Manor Hotel","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1375__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Situated in possibly the most beautiful valley in the Brecon Beacons National Park on the fringes of the pretty and sophisticated market town of Crickhowell, the views here are humbling.\n\nThe family owned Manor hotel sits at the foot of the ancient fortress, Table Mountain. With its striking white exterior against the vivid green backdrop of the Black Mountains this Manor House makes a bold statement.\n\nWith 23 individually styled bedrooms, the Manor\u2019s interior is honest, friendly and welcoming to all. Whether you are planning an outdoor activity break on the mountains, water, or in the air, our facilities are ideally suited to help you rest, recharge and recover. We have the only indoor heated swimming pool and leisure facilities in the nearby area, with sauna, Jacuzzi, and steam pool at your disposal.\n\nOur bistro overlooks a valley encroached by an impressive escarpment and the river Usk. Food is of great importance to us, fresh, tasty, seasonal and wholesome of which 90% of the meat and poultry on our menus comes directly from the family farm just seven miles down the road. - thats what you call local !\n\nWe think our hotel is the perfect Welsh country get away \u2013 come rain or shine, what ever you want to do, The Manor provides the ideal, affordable break in a clean, green, natural environment.\n\nSir George Everest was born here at our hotel in 1790! His pioneering mapping work led him to the Himalayas, and the highest peak in the world was named after him in 1865 \u2013 Mount Everest.\n\nDon't forget to take a look at our Taste Inn Wales websitewww.tasteinnwales.com to view all the very lastest news, events, and happenings within all 3 of our venues.....","url":"\/businesses\/2775"}},{"id":"manor_hotel_restaurant","lat":51.8660133,"lon":-3.1405756,"enhanced":true,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Manor Hotel Restaurant","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1375__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Situated in possibly the most beautiful valley in the Brecon Beacons National Park on the fringes of the pretty and sophisticated market town of Crickhowell, the views here are humbling.\n\nThe family owned Manor hotel sits at the foot of the ancient fortress, Table Mountain. With its striking white exterior against the vivid green backdrop of the Black Mountains this Manor House makes a bold statement.\n\nOur bistro overlooks a valley encroached by an impressive escarpment and the river Usk. Food is of great importance to us, fresh, tasty, seasonal and wholesome of which 90% of the meat and poultry on our menus comes directly from the family farm just seven miles down the road. - thats what you call local !\n\nWe think our hotel is the perfect Welsh country get away \u2013 come rain or shine, what ever you want to do, The Manor provides the ideal, affordable break in a clean, green, natural environment.\n\nSir George Everest was born here at our hotel in 1790! His pioneering mapping work led him to the Himalayas, and the highest peak in the world was named after him in 1865 \u2013 Mount Everest.\n\nDon't forget to take a look at our Taste Inn Wales websitewww.tasteinnwales.com to view all the very lastest news, events, and happenings within all 3 of our venues.....","url":"\/businesses\/3321"}},[],{"id":"nantyffin_cider_mill_inn","lat":51.8734242,"lon":-3.1678539,"enhanced":null,"popup":{"title":"Nantyffin Cider Mill Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/2784"}},{"id":"nicholls","lat":51.8242307,"lon":-3.0202045,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Nicholls","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3382"}},{"id":"number_eighteen","lat":51.8589228,"lon":-3.1374194,"enhanced":true,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Number Eighteen","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_2883__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Number Eighteen Cafe is located on the high street in Crickhowell, situated in the beautiful surroundings of the Brecon Beacons National Park.\r\n\r\nWe offer a range of hot and cold drinks, hot and cold food including our number eighteen favourites and some delicious home made treats. With the best coffee for miles, we\u2019re open during the day, every day of the week.","url":"\/businesses\/2789"}},{"id":"old_rectory_barn","lat":51.821787,"lon":-3.110139,"enhanced":null,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Old Rectory Barn","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1755__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Old Rectory Barn offers 5 star, self-catering accommodation within the Brecon Beacons National Park, has wonderful views and is close to the Monmouthshire - Brecon canal.The barn is set in five acres above the village of Maesygwartha and is an excellent base for exploring this beautiful and historic area. The Barn was renovated to the highest standards with many original features including stunning oak beams. The Barn has a GOLD green tourism business award so with rainwater harvesting and solar water heating we can help you have an eco friendly holiday. Accommodation: Old Rectory Barn offers flexible accommodation, available as one large property,&nbsp;with an internal link, that sleeps up to ten guests or as two independent cottages &ndash; the Loft and Stables. The Stables accommodates four people (twin and double bedroom) and the Loft sleeps four to six people (twin and large family bedroom). - All bedrooms have ensuite bathrooms. - Both cottages have their own kitchen\/dining\/living areas and the modern kitchens are fully equipped with fridge, electric oven, hob, dishwasher, microwave etc. - TV with Freeview\/DVD and CD player - Large garden with BBQ facilities. - Utility room with washing machine, dryer and freezer. - Drying room for outdoor gear and secure storage for bicycles. - Welcome pack of local produce provided for all self-catering guests. - Wi-Fi - Well-behaved dogs welcome. Guestbook Comments: 'I don't want to leave! Gorgeous views everywhere you look, comfortable modern accommodation in an older setting. We got the children to walk every day and even admit they liked it! Discovered a waterfall walk in the village which was a surprise.' 'Another relaxing stay in this wonderful barn. Thanks to Hilary and Graham for their hospitality - looking forward to our next visit.' &nbsp;'Extremely impressed with the excellent facilities and well thought out extras - absolutely love the 'green- ness' of this eco cottage. Highly recommended.'","url":"\/businesses\/2794"}},{"id":"oriel_cric_gallery","lat":51.8583347,"lon":-3.135938,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Oriel Cric Gallery","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3313"}},{"id":"pregge_mill","lat":51.8660133,"lon":-3.1405756,"enhanced":null,"popup":{"title":"Pregge Mill","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/2813"}},{"id":"red_hart_cottage","lat":51.8767119,"lon":-3.1068099,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Red Hart Cottage","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_3350__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Situated in the Brecon Beacons National Park in the heart of the Black Mountains, and a 25 minute drive from the Brecon Beacons, Red Hart Cottage boasts a wealth of period features, and is an ideal base from which to explore the spectacular scenery of the surrounding area. Red Hart Cottage is located in the friendly village of Llanbedr and is a minute's walk from the village pub, the Red Lion. Our self-catering Cottage dates from the 16th century and retains many original features such as oak beams, stone spiral staircase and Inglenook fireplace. It accommodates up to 5 adults or children aged 15 or over in two double bedrooms and a sofa in the living room, which converts to an extra bed. The main bedroom has an ensuite bathroom and there is also a downstairs cloakroom with toilet and washbasin, a conservatory and decking area with breathtaking mountain views and off road parking on the driveway. Ideal for families or couples, our two bed and breakfast rooms, a double and a twin (bunk beds) offer complete privacy being located in a self-contained annexe of the house. They have their own private bathroom and dining room, in which a self-serve continental breakfast is provided, and a separate entrance enabling guests to come and go at their convenience. Red Hart Cottage is conveniently situated for walking and cycling in the Black Mountains, with many walks and cycle trails accessible straight from the door. We are also a short drive from the Brecon Beacon mountains, Abergavenny, Brecon Town and Hay on Wye. Crickhowell is a 5 minute drive away and has many fine restaurants and cafes, banks, a post office, chemist, grocers, butchers and bakery. The Dragons Head pub in the neighbouring village of Llangenny can be relied upon for excellent food, a warm welcome and friendly service. Wales' capital city Cardiff, is an hour's drive away, or 40 minutes by train from Abergavenny, and there are many beautiful beaches within a 2 hour drive.","url":"\/businesses\/3623"}},{"id":"red_lion_inn","lat":51.8767119,"lon":-3.1068099,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Red Lion Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3174"}},{"id":"silver_birch_framing","lat":51.8579779,"lon":-3.1402852,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Silver Birch Framing","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3446"}},{"id":"six_bells_inn","lat":51.8586733,"lon":-3.1399688,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Six Bells Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3217"}},{"id":"the_bear_hotel","lat":51.8594741,"lon":-3.1371283999999,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"The Bear Hotel ","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_7021__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"A former coaching inn, The Bear at Crickhowell has been welcoming guests for 500 years and still extends the same warmth, comfort, cosy atmosphere, good food and wide selection of drinks as ever before.\r\nYou can eat and drink with friendly locals in the historic bar &ndash; with its oak beams, wooden floors and open fires &ndash; or in the more intimate settings of our restaurants. In the summer, we&rsquo;ll serve you in our beautiful gardens, surrounded by fragrant flowers and shaded by trees.\r\nGuests can stay in oak-beamed rooms just as stagecoach passengers did or in more modern suites, some with spa baths.\r\nAll of this in the charming town of Crickhowell, surrounded by the stunning scenery of the Brecon Beacons National Park, yet just over two hours from London and around an hour from Bristol, Cardiff, Swansea or Birmingham.","url":"\/businesses\/3165"}},{"id":"the_beaufort_china_gourmet","lat":51.8584621,"lon":-3.1367107999999,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Beaufort China Gourmet","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3230"}},{"id":"the_bell_inn","lat":51.8403267,"lon":-3.1055688,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Bell Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3208"}},{"id":"chateau_the","lat":51.8447649,"lon":-3.1173634,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Chateau Cottage","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_4691__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Built in 1867 in the grounds of a country house, Chateau Cottage is a self contained holiday cottage&nbsp;near the town of Crickhowell in the&nbsp;Brecon Beacons National Park. &nbsp;&nbsp;It is a perfect base for walking, mountain biking, fishing and horseriding.&nbsp;The cottage has 2 bedrooms (1 double and 1 twin)&nbsp;and an open plan lounge\/dining area\/kitchen downstairs.&nbsp; The shower room and separate toilet are also downstairs.There is a large enclosed mature garden&nbsp;of approximately half an acre adjacent to the cottage that has a paved&nbsp;patio with a table, chairs and BBQ as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;benches, loungers and another table and chairs&nbsp;in the&nbsp;garden area.&nbsp; Located in the midst of the Black Mountains and Brecon Beacons there are many walks directly from the cottage - Horseshoe Walk and Sugarloaf - as well as a delightful walk alongside the River Usk into Crickhowell with a variety of&nbsp;shops and restaurants.&nbsp; The cottage is very pet friendly and we welcome visitors that have more than one pet.The nearest public house is the Blue Bell&nbsp;- a&nbsp;10 minute walk from the cottage - which has weekly quizzes and music as well as a restaurant.&nbsp;&nbsp; We also have 2 mountain bikes available for holidaymakers to use as well as the loan of OS maps and walking books.","url":"\/businesses\/2709"}},{"id":"coach_horse_the","lat":51.8701706,"lon":-3.2329282000001,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Coach and Horses Tavern","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3220"}},{"id":"the_corn_exchange_inn","lat":51.8276506,"lon":-3.0967548,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Corn Exchange Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3198"}},{"id":"the_dragons_head","lat":51.8568517,"lon":-3.1056834999999,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Dragons Head","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3176"}},{"id":"the_farmers_arms","lat":51.9048729,"lon":-3.1914621,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Farmers Arms","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3203"}},{"id":"the_kestrel_inn","lat":51.885428037663,"lon":-3.2078610544922,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Kestrel Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3201"}},{"id":"the_neuadd_cottages","lat":51.845482,"lon":-3.156273,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"The Neuadd Cottages","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1779__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Great views, walks from the door.... The Neuadd holiday cottages are located 5 mins drive from Crickhowell's great pubs, cafes, and shops in the Brecon Beacons in South Wales. Our self catering accommodation is easily accessible from good roads yet tucked away in a beautiful and quiet location enjoying open views of The Sugar Loaf, Table Mountain and Llangattock Mountain (all three can be walked from the door). There are canal and riverside walks from the door and if you're cyclists like us then there are excellent road and mountain bike rides close by. There's space here to sit out, fettle your bike, soak up the views, check over your canoe, do some painting, or photograph the sunrise over The Sugar Loaf. Did we mention the views? Many of the photos on this website are taken from our land including the one above. The Neuadd Cottages are a recent conversion (2002) of barns and stables. All eight cottages have views and are comfortably appointed with 4 star Visit Wales accreditation. All are non-smoking, some accept dogs by arrangement whilst in some pets are not allowed. The cottages can be rented individually, or are available as a group to gather family and friends","url":"\/businesses\/2838"}},{"id":"racehorse_inn","lat":51.7938355,"lon":-3.1344902,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Racehorse Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3236"}},{"id":"the_vine_tree","lat":51.8552171,"lon":-3.1421902,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Vine Tree","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3189"}},{"id":"ty_gwyn","lat":51.8624462,"lon":-3.1393962,"enhanced":null,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Ty Gwyn B&B","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_2334__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/2851"}},{"id":"ty_tal","lat":51.8586733,"lon":-3.1399688,"enhanced":null,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Ty Tal","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_2927__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Ty Tal B&B is located in Crickhowell, a few minutes walk from the High Street. It is a Victorian townhouse that has been completely refurbished to provide modern, comfortable and tasteful accommodation. Breakfasts include locally sourced ingredients and delicious homemade & vegetarian options. There is a private car park and a safe lock-up for bikes. The proprietor is a keen walker and can offer advice on hiking in the mountains.","url":"\/businesses\/2854"}},{"id":"webbs_of_crickhowell","lat":51.8589228,"lon":-3.1374194,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Webbs of Crickhowell","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3394"}},{"id":"wern_watkin","lat":51.8350185,"lon":-3.150895,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Wern Watkin","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1950__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"A magical location for outdoor activities, educational field studies and training courses.\r\n\r\nA 5 Star Bunkhouse!  \r\n  \r\nWern Watkin is located high up on Mynnedd Llangattock near the escarpment and offers direct walking access to the mountainside, ancient woodland, caves, cliffs and industrial heritage. Our guests include families, scouts, ramblers, canoeists, cyclists, cavers, training groups, educational groups, families, and social groups.\r\n\r\nThe Watkin Bunkhouse is a converted stone built barn for 30 people. It also operates as YHA Llangattock Mountain. We are a Visit Wales 5 star graded bunkhouse and also accredited as walker and cyclist friendly. Our links with YHA scheme gives you assurance of the standards that we offer. The bunkhouse sleeps up to thirty people in seven fully en-suite bedrooms. There is a massive dining room\/seating area and a wonderful outdoor space opening out onto ancient woodlands. There is under-floor heating throughout, excellent drying facilities and ample hot water. For further details, please take our 360 tour!\r\n\r\nActivities\r\nOur location is simply wonderful for an enormous range of activities. We can arrange a wide range of outdoor pursuits using local experienced and qualified instructors. However many of our guests just use us as a base for a reunion and just hang out on site with the children playing in streams and woodlands!\r\n\r\n","url":"\/businesses\/2861"}}];
